metadata.name: Learning to Fly #12
metadata.description:
It all started with @chilltulpa saying in fxhash discord "I wish i could make art" and @mknol answering with a few lines of code to create generative art... It was more than enough for me to finally dive in, and try to make something. 

Learning is the key here, learning is being alive.
This is me learning, this is a beginning, I'm learning to fly.

metadata.name: tr4ns4ctions #57
metadata.description:
Tr4ns4ctions is a series of real-time animations that use pixels to create an abstraction of the movement of values. The pixels are constantly rearranging, being transferred from offer to taker, liquify, appear and disappear. They are forming endless compositions, sometimes intransparent or with strange spins.

The level of abstraction has been set to a 2x pixel size and the color palette of the NES with 12 different color modes. 16 pixel patterns serve as the fundamental building blocks and a simplex noise field determines the direction of movement.

click || space => pause/unpause

View all tr4ns4ctions at https://tr4ns4ctions.com

Kim Asendorf, 2022

metadata.name: "String" Theory #24
metadata.description:
Our world is breathing, and you can see the flow of world life, how strings shape this life?

“In string theory, one of the vibrational states of the string gives rise to the graviton, a quantum mechanical particle that carries gravitational force. Thus string theory is a theory of quantum gravity.”
—  Becker, Becker and Schwarz

metadata.name: The Samsara-Verse #31
metadata.description:
Samsara is the endless Wheel of Life, where uncountable numbers of souls ceaselessly wander through its 6 realms - Deva-gati (abode of the gods), Asura-gati (demi-gods), Preta-gati (hungry ghosts), Naraka-gati (Hell), Tiryagyoni-gati (animals), Manusya-gati (the human realm).
 
These realms are interleaved with manifold planes of existence separated by the thinnest of veils.
And yet - these hives of endless activity are but a small fraction of the totality of the metaverse, as multitudes of unformed universes, as yet mere sketches, await their blooming.

This artwork consists of both a visual aspect and a sonic representation echoing the voices of the denizens of the various planes of the Samsara-Verse.

Once the piece has finished drawing, click or press "m" to unmute the soundtrack.
Press "s" to save the image as a ".png" file (4800x3600 pixels).

Collaborative work by Geoffrey Crayon - art design and coding - and Cylonix (JJClark) - sound design. The audio samples used (in addition to generative drones) are from Loopology and Splice.

metadata.name: Crosswords #3
metadata.description:
Crosswords is an abstract representation of the challenges that life puts in front of us daily. We just need to find the right answer that fits the empty tiles to accomplish everything. Impossible is nothing.

Color palettes are inspired by the great artworks of Donald Judd.

By refreshing the screen on different window sizes the artwork will adapt and the position and dimension of the tiles might change.
In this way, I want to mimic the infinite crosswords we need to solve in our lifetime.

hit 's' on live view to save a png of the current view.

metadata.name: MetaMountains #88
metadata.description:
Beautiful MetaMountains to stare and escape from reality, sometimes they will look like any other mountain, and Sometimes while you look at them you will have the feeling of seeing the terrain of a planet in a distant galaxy.

Is that a regular mountain? No! It's a MetaMountain! You may even witness the rise of two suns or two moons.

No fancy features, just waves, and shapes with 8 hand-picked color schemes. Sit back and enjoy.

----

Color schemes:

[] Japan Mountains
[] Farm Mountains
[] Summer Mountains
[] Carbon Mountains
[] Arizona Mountains
[] Nordic Mountains
[] MonoDay Mountains
[] MonoNight Mountains

metadata.name: reborn #209
metadata.description:
This is an album of cities too ideal to ever materialise.

It consists of 256 algorithmically generated plans that resemble drawings of Vincenzo Scamozzi, Pietro Cataneo, Filarete and other theorists of the Italian Renaissance. The cities differ in size, the grid of the streets, the landscape around them and the people that inhabit their utopian walls. They carry names that are Italian exonyms of real European cities, drawing a vision of a different world that enacts a mixture of military perfection with social superiority. Flawless, harmonious, unconquerable and utterly impossible.

History brought us many theories about ideal cities, but very few examples exist today. Italian Palmanova or Polish Zamość are the few to remind us how hard it is to shape reality according to ideals. When confronted with the material world, its idealism becomes the city's grates foe.

To zoom, press a mouse button over the image or touch the screen. To pan, keep the mouse pressed and move it around.

metadata.name: Pasghetti Tango #6
metadata.description:
A study in Dense Abstract Expressionism (e.g. Lee Krasner) done using emulation of felt pen depiction of a tangle of wet spaghetti noodles.

Press "s" to save image in a .png format file.

metadata.name: Taiga #97
metadata.description:
Generate Tall pines, spruces in atmospheric environment. I need to draw anything I feel around, any story, any relations and any environment. colors are beautiful but can not describe many moments and many atmospheres. this gray scale feeling is about my world. Feeling full of loneliness and sadness, but I know it's generated in my mind. it's not real!

All is generative! Features and variations exist in tree types, atmosphere background-foregrounds, flyings.

=========== Controls ===========
🔸 Press F key to change view.
🔸 Press S key to save high resolution image.

metadata.name: COMPOSITION X #19
metadata.description:
I sat at my canvas, feeling the urge to create something new and different.
I began to experiment with different colors and shapes, letting my intuition guide me.
As the composition took shape, I found myself lost in the process.
Minutes passed as I layered and blended colors, creating a dynamic and ever-changing grid.

Finally, I stepped back to admire my creation, feeling a sense of satisfaction and fulfillment.

metadata.name: Curtains #83
metadata.description:
Curtains

While learning more about flow fields, as an intermediate step, the first version of this came out.
The artwork creates a set of lines; the first point of the lines are anchors, which can be in a straight line, sinus wave, or tangent function.
The second point is set by calculating the angle from the first using Perlin noise.

The project features 10 different hand-picked color schemes.

Actions:
--------------
Press [s] to save
--------------


Created using p5.js
